ui_data.label: Data Asset
ui_data.description: Pull in data from remote data sources using connections, or pull in data from a file.

ui_data.label: User Input
ui_data.description: Easily create synthetic dataâ€”either from scratch or by altering existing data.

ui_data.label: Sim Gen
ui_data.description: Generate simulated data automatically or with user-specified statistical distributions.

categories.label: Record Operations
categories.description: This category defines operations on records

ui_data.label: Select
ui_data.description: Select or discard a subset of records from the data stream based on a specific condition.

ui_data.label: Sample
ui_data.description: Select a subset of records for analysis, or specify a proportion of records to discard.

ui_data.label: Sort
ui_data.description: Sort records into ascending or descending order based on the values of one or more fields.

ui_data.label: Balance
ui_data.description: Correct imbalances in datasets so they conform to specified test criteria.

ui_data.label: Distinct
ui_data.description: Find or remove duplicate records in your data, or create a single, composite record from a group of duplicate records.

ui_data.label: Aggregate
ui_data.description: Replace a sequence of input records with summary, aggregated output records.

ui_data.label: Merge
ui_data.description: Take multiple input records and create a single output record containing all or some of the input fields.

ui_data.label: Append
ui_data.description: Combine datasets with similar structures but different data.

ui_data.label: Space-Time-Boxes
ui_data.description: An STB is an alphanumeric string that represents a regularly shaped region of space and time.

ui_data.label: Streaming TS
ui_data.description: Build and score time series models in one step.

ui_data.label: SMOTE
ui_data.description: To perform over-sampling using SMOTE - Synthetic Minority Over-sampling Technique

ui_data.label: RFM Aggregate
ui_data.description: Take historical transaction data, strip away unused data, and combine all remaining transaction data into one row.

categories.label: Field Operations
categories.description: This category defines operations on fields

ui_data.label: Auto Data Prep
ui_data.description: Prepare your data for model building quickly and easily, without needing prior knowledge of the statistical concepts involved.

ui_data.label: Type
ui_data.description: Specify field metadata and properties that are invaluable to modeling.

ui_data.label: Filter
ui_data.description: Rename or exclude fields at any point in a flow.

ui_data.label: Derive
ui_data.description: Modify data values or create new fields from one or more existing fields.

ui_data.label: Filler
ui_data.description: Replace field values and change storage. Often used with a Type node to replace missing values.

ui_data.label: Reclassify
ui_data.description: Transform one set of categorical values to another. Useful for collapsing categories or regrouping data for analysis.

ui_data.label: Binning
ui_data.description: Automatically create new nominal fields based on the values of one or more existing continuous fields.

ui_data.label: RFM Analysis
ui_data.description: Examine recent customer purchases (recency), how often they purchased (frequency), and how much they spent (monetary).

ui_data.label: Ensemble
ui_data.description: Combines two or more model nuggets to obtain more accurate predictions than can be gained from any of the individual models.

ui_data.label: Partition
ui_data.description: Generate a partition field that splits data into separate subsets or samples for the training, testing, and validation stages of model building.

ui_data.label: SetToFlag
ui_data.description: Derive flag fields based on the categorical values defined for one or more nominal fields.

ui_data.label: Restructure
ui_data.description: Generate multiple fields based on the values of a nominal or flag field.

ui_data.label: Transpose
ui_data.description: Swap the data in rows and columns so that fields become records and records become fields.

ui_data.label: Field Reorder
ui_data.description: Define the natural order for displaying fields downstream.

ui_data.label: History
ui_data.description: Create new fields containing data from fields in previous records (most often used for sequential data, such as time series data).

ui_data.label: Time Intervals
ui_data.description: Specify intervals and derive a new time field for estimating or forecasting.

ui_data.label: Anonymize
ui_data.description: Disguise field names, field values, or both when working with data that's to be included in a model downstream of the node.

ui_data.label: Reproject
ui_data.description: Change the coordinate system for fields that can't be reprojected automatically.

ui_data.label: Charts
ui_data.description: Launch the chart builder and create chart definitions to save with your flow.

ui_data.label: Plot
ui_data.description: Shows the relationship between numeric fields.

ui_data.label: Multiplot
ui_data.description: A special type of plot that displays multiple Y fields over a single X field.

ui_data.label: Time plot
ui_data.description: View one or more time series plotted over time.

ui_data.label: Distribution
ui_data.description: Shows the occurrence of symbolic (non-numeric) values, such as mortgage type or gender, in a dataset.

ui_data.label: Histogram
ui_data.description: Shows the occurrence of values for numeric fields.

ui_data.label: Collection
ui_data.description: Shows the distribution of values for one numeric field relative to the values of another.

ui_data.label: Web
ui_data.description: Shows the strength of relationships between values of two or more symbolic fields.

ui_data.label: Evaluation
ui_data.description: Evaluate and compare predictive models to choose the best model for your application.

ui_data.label: Auto Classifier
ui_data.description: Estimates and compares models to try out a variety of approaches for nominal and binary data.

ui_data.label: Auto Numeric
ui_data.description: Estimates and compares models to try out a variety of approaches for a continuous numeric range.

ui_data.label: Auto Cluster
ui_data.description: Estimates and compares clustering models that identify groups of records with similar characteristics.

ui_data.label: Bayes Net
ui_data.description: Build a probability model to establish the likelihood of occurrences by using seemingly unlinked attributes.

ui_data.label: C5.0
ui_data.description: Build either a decision tree or a ruleset by splitting the sample based on the field that provides the maximum information gain.

ui_data.label: C&R Tree
ui_data.description: Tree-based classification and prediction method that splits training records into segments with similar output field values.

ui_data.label: CHAID
ui_data.description: Build decision trees by using chi-square statistics to identify optimal splits.

ui_data.label: Quest
ui_data.description: Build decision trees by using a binary classification method.

ui_data.label: Tree-AS
ui_data.description: Build decision trees using either a CHAID or Exhaustive CHAID model.

ui_data.label: Random Trees
ui_data.description: Build an ensemble model that consists of multiple decision trees.

ui_data.label: Random Forest
ui_data.description: Implement a bagging algorithm with a tree model as the base model.

ui_data.label: Decision List
ui_data.description: Identify subgroups or segments that show a higher or lower likelihood of a binary (yes or no) outcome relative to the overall sample.

ui_data.label: Time Series
ui_data.description: Estimate and build exponential smoothing, ARIMA, or multivariate ARIMA models and produce forecasts.

ui_data.label: TCM
ui_data.description: Create a temporal causal model to discover key causal relationships in time series data.

ui_data.label: GenLin
ui_data.description: Build an equation that relates the input field values to the output field values.

ui_data.label: GLMM
ui_data.description: Creates a generalized linear mixed model that extends the linear model.

ui_data.label: GLE
ui_data.description: Identify the dependent variable that's linearly related to the factors and covariates via a specified link function.

ui_data.label: Linear
ui_data.description: Classify records based on the values of numeric input fields.

ui_data.label: Linear-AS
ui_data.description: Classify records based on the values of numeric input fields.

ui_data.label: Regression
ui_data.description: Classify records based on the values of numeric input fields.

ui_data.label: LSVM
ui_data.description: Use a linear support vector machine to classify data.

ui_data.label: Logistic
ui_data.description: Classify records based on the values of categorical input fields.

ui_data.label: Neural Net
ui_data.description: Approximate a wide range of predictive models with minimal demands on model structure and assumption.

ui_data.label: KNN
ui_data.description: Find patterns of data without requiring an exact match to any stored patterns, or cases.

ui_data.label: Cox
ui_data.description: Build a predictive model for time-to-even data.

ui_data.label: PCA/Factor
ui_data.description: Provides powerful data-reduction techniques to reduce the complexity of your data.

ui_data.label: SVM
ui_data.description: Use a support vector machine to classify data.

ui_data.label: Feature Selection
ui_data.description: Identify fields that are most important for a given analysis.

ui_data.label: Discriminant
ui_data.description: Build a predictive model for group membership.

ui_data.label: SLRM
ui_data.description: Predict which offers are most appropriate for customers and the probability of the offers being accepted.

ui_data.label: STP
ui_data.description: Has many potential applications such as energy management for buildings, or public transport planning.

ui_data.label: Association Rules
ui_data.description: Automatically find associations that you could find manually using visualization techniques.

ui_data.label: Apriori
ui_data.description: Discover association rules in your data.

ui_data.label: Carma
ui_data.description: Use an association rules discovery algorithm to discover association rules in your data.

ui_data.label: Sequence
ui_data.description: Discover patterns in sequential or time-oriented data.

ui_data.label: Kohonen
ui_data.description: Cluster your dataset into distinct groups when you don't know what those groups are at the beginning.

ui_data.label: Anomaly
ui_data.description: Identify outliers, or unusual cases, in your data.

ui_data.label: K-Means
ui_data.description: Use a cluster method to cluster your dataset into distinct groups when you don't know what those groups are at the beginning.

ui_data.label: TwoStep
ui_data.description: Cluster your dataset into distinct groups when you don't know what those groups are at first.

ui_data.label: TwoStep-AS
ui_data.description: Use this exploratory toolÂ  to reveal natural groupings (clusters) within your dataset.

ui_data.label: Isotonic-AS
ui_data.description: Isotonic Regression belongs to the family of regression algorithms. Implemented in Spark.

ui_data.label: K-Means-AS
ui_data.description: Cluster data points into a predefined number of clusters.

ui_data.label: KDE Modeling
ui_data.description: Walks the line between unsupervised learning, feature engineering, and data modeling.

ui_data.label: Gaussian Mixture
ui_data.description: CExposes the core features and commonly used parameters of the Gaussian Mixture Python library.

ui_data.label: XGBoost-AS
ui_data.description: xgboostas.desc

ui_data.label: XGBoost Tree
ui_data.description: Uses an advanced implementation of a gradient boosting algorithm with a tree model as the base model.

ui_data.label: XGBoost Linear
ui_data.description: Uses an advanced implementation of a gradient boosting algorithm with a linear model as the base model.

ui_data.label: One-Class SVM
ui_data.description: Detects the soft boundary of a given set of samples, to then classify new points as belonging to that set or not.

ui_data.label: MultiLayerPerceptron-AS
ui_data.description: A classifier based on the feedforward artificial neural network. Consists of multiple layers.

ui_data.label: HDBSCAN
ui_data.description: Uses unsupervised learning to find clusters, or dense regions, of a data set.

categories.label: Text Analytics
categories.description: This category defines Text Mining operations

ui_data.label: Language Identifier
ui_data.description: Identify the natural language of a text field within your source data.

ui_data.label: Text Link Analysis
ui_data.description: Identify relationships between the concepts in the text data based on known patterns.

ui_data.label: Text Mining
ui_data.description: Extract key concepts from text and create categories with these concepts and other data.

ui_data.label: Table
ui_data.description: Create a table that lists the values in your data.

ui_data.label: Matrix
ui_data.description: Create a table that shows relationships between fields.

ui_data.label: Analysis
ui_data.description: Evaluate the ability of a model to generate accurate predictions.

ui_data.label: Data Audit
ui_data.description: Get a comprehensive first look at your data, presented in an easy-to-read matrix.

ui_data.label: Transform
ui_data.description: Perform a rapid visual assessment of the best transformation to use.

ui_data.label: Statistics
ui_data.description: Get basic summary information about numeric fields.

ui_data.label: Means
ui_data.description: Compare the means between independent groups or between pairs of related fields to test whether a significant difference exists.

ui_data.label: Report
ui_data.description: Create formatted reports containing fixed text, data, or other expressions derived from your data.

ui_data.label: Set Globals
ui_data.description: Scans your data and computes summary values that can be used in CLEM expressions.

ui_data.label: Sim Fit
ui_data.description: Fits a set of candidate statistical distributions to each field in your data.

ui_data.label: Data Asset Export
ui_data.description: Write to remote data sources using connections.
